&lt;li&gt;Manage business plan execution, including but not limited to launching new products, delivery of product marketing and training support, meeting customer deadlines, managing customer orders, and supporting forecasting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead regular business reviews with developing accounts and provide account updates, promotional activities, and market trends&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure timely communication of pricing, orders, credits, and sales support&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Visit customers regularly within the market to ensure Olaplex standards and objectives are achieved, and to assess and execute key opportunities to maximize sales and profitability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Account Support&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Account Managers with account management tasks, including promotional calendar updates, order tracking, and internal coordination&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in preparing joint business plan materials, reports, and presentation decks&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respond to day-to-day customer requests under supervision&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Execution&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate the execution of brand and education activations with partnerships from the Marketing and Education teams&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor product availability, pricing communication, and on-time delivery&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with basic sales and KPI reporting as needed&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You: &amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2-4 years of experience in sales support, account coordination, or a related commercial role&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
